Effort estimation:
 - EI: Dev 12h, INT 8h, ACC 4h, PROD 2h

 - QA: INT 6h, ACC 4h, PROD 2h

FHCS wants to enhance the TSM configuration. The followings changes will be added:
h2. 1- To add new criterions for the Slot calculation,

i.e. a new columns will be added to MD table "slot_calculation" for each field:

1.1 - {*}Stackability{*}: New text field will be added on the Booking with possible values "non_stackable" or "stackable". The column "stackability" on table "slot_calculation" will be added too. The default value will be "non_stackable" Carrier/Shipper user will be able to modify the field in the OB creation menu before the creation of the booking and the slot calculation will be re-calculated accordingly.

Similar to current "Master carton" field, you can copy the configuration of that field in the bundle.

1.2 - {*}Gate{*}: New column "gate" will be added to the table as another criteria for the slot calculation. The OB will be created without gate (only location), and the value "All gates" for the MD table "slot_calculation" will be taken during the slot calculation process. “All gates” option will be for the cases where the gate is not selected yet or in case there is no result found for the selected gate. Once the gate is selected the slot length is updated so it will be re-calculated during the booking creation.

1.3 - {*}Supplier code{*}: new field is already mapped from TOPS (supplier) to TA (loading_nr) on delivery level). The field will be exported to the OB and will be included as another column ("supplier_code") for slot calculation . It will be optional in the MD table. In case no result is found in the table with supplier number (loading_nr) of the delivery, the row with the value empty will be chosen.

1.4 - {*}Material number{*}: The field "Code" in TOPS (Material Order/Shipping Unit/Line ID) is already mapped to in TA (material_number in delivery Item level). Consequently one delivery can have more than one value of "material_number".

New field "special_material" will be available in the Booking. Optional, it will have values Yes/No. It will be calculated during the slot_calculation process: 
 * There will be a new MD table "Material_number_slot_length" with one single column "material_numbers". It will be the list of special material numbers. Every time that the slot calculation process occurs, the list of material numbers will be checked. If one of the material numbers of the items in the delivery contains match with the list in the table, special_material will be Yes. Otherwise the value will be No.

Also, the new column of Material number in slot_calculation table will be "special_material". It will mandatory and with the possible values Yes/No. The query of the table will use the homonymous field.
h2. 2. origin and destination location

To map origin and destination location names of the delivery to the OB. It will be taken from loading station/company_name and unloading station/company_name of the delivery. They will be stored on new custom fields "origin" and "destination" on the Booking.

We need to do the following adjustments:

#1 To map "delivery.name" from delivery level to OB creation. It will map with a custom field "material_order_reference" in the Booking  

#2 To map "company_name" from delivery level to OB creation. It will map with a custom field "collection_location_name" in the Booking in case it is a loading station (pick up).

#4 Currently customer is using excel files for importing and creating Open Bookings. We should add the following columns in the Excel import:

4.2 - Special Material Number --> Optional. Yes/No values. In case it is empty, it will be considered as "No". It will be mapped with "special_material" in the OB and used for searching in the slot calculation.

Gate or stackability will be missed as they shipper does not know the values when the OB is created.

items.fromString:
FHCS wants to enhance the TSM configuration. The followings changes will be added:
h2. 1- To add new criterions for the Slot calculation,

i.e. a new columns will be added to MD table "slot_calculation" for each field:


1.1 - {*}Stackability{*}: New text field will be added on the Booking with possible values "non_stackable" or "stackable". The column "stackability" on table "slot_calculation" will be added too. The default value will be "non_stackable" Carrier/Shipper user will be able to modify the field in the OB creation menu before the creation of the booking and the slot calculation will be re-calculated accordingly.

Similar to current "Master carton" field, you can copy the configuration of that field in the bundle.

1.2 - {*}Gate{*}: New column "gate" will be added to the table as another criteria for the slot calculation. The OB will be created without gate (only location), and the value "All gates" for the MD table "slot_calculation" will be taken during the slot calculation process. Once the gate is selected the slot length is updated so itt will be re-calculated during the booking creation.

1.3 - {*}Supplier code{*}: new field is already mapped from TOPS (supplier) to TA (loading_nr) on delivery level). The field will be exported to the OB and will be included as another column ("supplier_code") for slot calculation . It will be optional in the MD table. In case no result is found in the table with the material number of the TO, the row with the value empty will be chosen.

1.4 - {*}Material number{*}: The field "Code" in TOPS (Material Order/Shipping Unit/Line ID) is already mapped to in TA (material_number in delivery Item level). Consequently one delivery can have more than one value of "material_number".

New field "special_material" will be available in the Booking. Optional, it will have values Yes/No. It will be calculated during the slot_calculation process: 
 * There will be a new MD table "Material_number_slot_length" with one single column "material_numbers". It will be the list of special material numbers. Every time that the slot calculation process occurs, the list of material numbers will be checked. If one of the material numbers of the items in the delivery contains match with the list in the table, special_material will be Yes. Otherwise the value will be No.

Also, the new column of Material number in slot_calculation table will be "special_material". It will mandatory and with the possible values Yes/No. The query of the table will use the homonymous field.
h2. 2. origin and destination location

To map origin and destination location names of the delivery to the OB. It will be taken from loading station/company_name and unloading station/company_name of the delivery. They will be stored on new custom fields "origin" and "destination" on the Booking.
